i cant believe my kids are nearing 14th months
time flies and you can never get it back thats what i keep reminding myself

i take them on evening walks while theyre still around 10kg but the window is closing  they are beginning to babble make incoherent sounds and occasionally say something that resembles language  and everyone around us is reading it into it
mommy thinks theyre saying mommy grandmas and aunties are biased in the other direction

personally i think my sons first words will be a version of hey google play jazz because we say that everyday 

marvin is predisposed to being fearless while my daughter milin is more cautious
milin started walking faster but marvin has caught up and is now climbing  they both know how to get attention and are not shy about using their voices
weve set up a montessori station but this is an area where theory and practice diverge
weve read the book taken some workshops and yet in the face of a 14 month old babies  theory goes out the window
well take it daybyday

there is no other profession where youre more frequently reminded of your age than in teaching

every semester

me mentions some pop culture reference in class
students i was literally born that exact year
me
got 2020 fatigue
lets take a trip down memory lane to everyone fav icon 90s sitcom
friends generally got 20  30 million views every episode for 10 years
but for two episodes in season 2 viewership jumped to 50 million views credit to guest starts julia roberts and jeanclaude van damme
after the first season the show runners mustve known they had something special so it was smart to book high profile actors to give the show a boost
heat maps are aesthetically more interesting to look at when theres range restriction in the data we see much more diversity in color for imdb ratings than viewership
when filtering for episodes with the highest ratings and viewership we get the seminal episodes in the shows history
these episodes for the most part advance the rossrachel and monicachandler story arc that form the backbone of the series
take away these 7 episodes and we get a completely different show
credit to the writer for imbuing the characters with a full range of emotions
while not part of the main plot joey and phoebe carry their fair share of the emotional work

one of the many things i didnt see coming in 2020 was that a large portion of my work would have a medical theme
precovid i had applied to a data visualization competition hosted at upenn at their flagship people analytics conference
this year they partnered with doctors without borders a medical humanitarian organization that delivers emergency aid to people affected by conflict epidemics and natural disasters

our task was to analyze data dating back to 1996 on their global workforce comprising 45000 people to understand the career paths of medical coordinators a toplevel exec position within the organization
excited to report that im a finalist for the competition
i was absolutely looking forward to presenting in philly visiting friends in nyc and soaking in the east coast again
alas the virus had other plans
as with practically every other conference in every other industry whartons people analytics conference transitioned to online remote only
we had to submit a final prerecorded video presentation instead i just submitted  fingers crossed

hello gsse fam

just wanted to share a prototype ive been working on with my medical doctor friend
its a dashboard designed to help hospitals manage important resource during a pandemic outbreak
although were on a pretty good trajectory in thailand one can never be too careful  and theres a possibility of a second or third wave of infections
so this dashboard can be used to see how various hospitals have to manage their staff space and supplies efficiently so they can service new patients
if anyone reading this knows of medical doctors or hospital administrators please feel free to share as its a workinprogress and were thirsty for feedback

excited to share a prototype of a hospital dashboard ive been working with my good friend 94345732048timothy dechaumphai to create to help smallmedium sized hospitals prepare just in case theres a second or third wave of covid19 infections not to mention the uncertainty around this virus
this is a tool to help visualize some resources a hospital  needs to manage in case of a surge in patients
to minimize complexity we focus on two primary types of data stock how many supplies staff and beds does the hospital have
and flow data how efficiently are patients being moved throughout the system
as a medical doctor whose worked in hospitalist and in hospital administration 94345732048timothy dechaumphai s input has been invaluable
in addition weve tried to incorporate literature on pandemic planning
its certainly been educational for me to learn about how hospitals must manage their resources during these challenging times
this is definitely a workinprogress so if you know any medical doctorsa a hospital administrators please share wed love to get some feedback and engagement to see if its worth developing further
this dashboard is made with r shiny and some javascript

you can play with the live app here 2httpspaulapivatshinyappsiodashboard_app

weve written an explainer here detailing various scenarios where hospital capacity becomes strained here  httpgetwyzecomhospitaldashboardprototypesurgecapacityscenarios

as major parts of the city shut down and we practice social distancing many of us fortunate to be able to work from home are beginning to question

 how long will we have to stay home and practice social distancing
how long will schools entertainment venues shut down
how long until small businesses run out of cashflow
how long before the economy goes into a deep recession
no one knows for sure
at this point there are more questions than answers because thereas not enough data to reliably answer much
what i think we can do is look at the data that is available to us
to that end iad like to focus on numbers that donat get as much attention from the media
to be sure there are lots of visualizations graphics and dashboard for tracking covid19 so i wanted to focus on one  important aspect itas growth
i made a dashboard tracking two types of growth  the familiar daytoday growth rate in total confirmed cases and growth factor

currently focused on thailand but hoping to add usitalyskoreasingapore for comparison

see here httpspaulapivatshinyappsiocovidgrowth 

this should give us some sense for where we are in the growth curve of this virus
if the growth factor is consistently between 115  125 or higher it means weall see a doubling in our total confirmed cases in about 5 days

read more here httpgetwyzecomgrowthfactor

if after a period of fast growth the number gets down to about 10 we might be at an inflection point where we might have peaked
thereas a lot of uncertainty and these are fundamentally lagging indicators so weare not doing any forecasting here
in creating this dashboard i ran into some interesting data challenges inconsistencies and availability

i wrote about those challenges and my temporary solution here httpgetwyzecomtrackingcovid19growth

iall be updating this dashboard manually everyday as new numbers become available

be safe and happy social distancing

im not sensing a sufficient level of urgency around me regarding  covid19 so im sharing some data and visualizations hoping to highlight an underreported aspect of the coronavirus
those who have been following the news are aware of the numbers  confirmed cases deaths and recovered  but these static numbers bury the lead of the story in my view
the important thing to grasp is the growth rate
not incremental growth but exponential growth
we tend to think linearly and thats a mistake in this situation
we feel for italy and we think maybe its just because they werent prepared
but the growth rates displayed in italy are present in many other countries
i think it would be foolish to think oh thats wont happen in my country
i think we need to move to remote workclasses practice social distancing immediately and frankly postpone weddings social gatherings conferences meetups etc
anything else is flirting with risk
please read on
at the end of the post i have a list of resources for individuals and organizational leaders

stay safe wash your hands and spend time with your family at home

been thinking about governance lately
effective governance gives us confidence that the organization we work for has not only our best interests at heart but customers stakeholders and wider community that we serve
without good governance you have no choice but to hope that your leader is virtuous and competent or a benevolent dictator
worst case scenario in cases where leaders lack virtue  competence effective governance checks and balances a strong board saves people from themselves

for public infrastructure networks ie blockchains the importance of governance is magnified 100x because there is no person to be single point of failure  and on the flip side no person to be accountable for in case something happens to public assets
in this post i borrow from the exciting multidisciplinary field of collective intelligence to exam how the ethereum network could tackle some of its governance challenges
